<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>go down to the wire • go under the wire</xh5><p> <i>go down to the wire</i>—(also: come down to the wire) continue to the very last moment or the very end: The game will <u>go down to the wire</u> but in the end the Uconn Huskies should pull away as national champions.</p><p><i>go under the wire</i>—(also: come under the wire) 1. be at the finishing-line of a racecourse: Like an irresistible, perfect piece of mechanism she sailed on; and <u>went under the wire</u> a clear winner.... 2. come at the last possible moment: It was not front page news and I guess <u>went under the wire</u> many places. The timing of this announcement was indeed bad. 3. get free from detention camp (surrounded by barbed wire) by flight: He hasn’t assimilated. He doesn’t want to be here. And he might <u>go under the wire</u> first chance he gets.</p> </entry>
